# LiveKit (piii) — realtime sessions for voice agents

## Docs-first (LiveKit changes fast)

- Prefer reading our integration doc first: `docs/integrations/livekit.md`.
- When implementing new LiveKit features, consult LiveKit docs (CLI/MCP/llms.txt) before writing code.
 - For transport-level concerns (SDK platforms, media/data, E2EE, self-hosting) consult the LiveKit Transport docs (`transport.md`) as well.

## Hosting note

- Keep LiveKit configuration **environment-driven** so we can use LiveKit Cloud or self-hosting without changing application code.

## Use the internal stack (do not re-implement)

Use:
- `src/lib/livekit/*`

Specifically:
- Token minting: `src/lib/livekit/tokens.ts`
- Room service: `src/lib/livekit/room-service.ts`
- Webhooks: `src/lib/livekit/webhooks.ts`

## Transport SDKs note

- Client apps should use the appropriate LiveKit client SDK (web/mobile/etc). In this repo, web uses `livekit-client`.
- Server orchestration should use `src/lib/livekit/*` (tokens/room service/webhooks) rather than ad-hoc SDK usage.

## Media note

- Model realtime audio/video as **published/subscribed tracks**.
- For track-level work, consult LiveKit Media docs (`transport/media.md`) and keep publish/subscribe + permissions explicit.

## Data note

- Prefer **text streams / byte streams / RPC** over raw data packets.
- Use participant attributes/metadata + room metadata only for **low-frequency** shared state.

## Webhook verification requirement

- Webhook verification MUST use the **raw request body string** (not parsed JSON).
- Always verify the `Authorization` header signature before trusting webhook payloads.

## Voice-agent architecture note

LiveKit is the transport/session layer; Gemini Live is the model voice layer.
For Gemini Live voice agents we only allow `gemini-3.1-flash-live-preview` (see `.cursor/rules/gemini-live-api.mdc`).

## Models note

- LiveKit docs cover many STT/LLM/TTS providers and realtime models.
- In Pi, **realtime voice agents must follow the Gemini Live policy** (don’t introduce selectable realtime models).

## Agents framework concepts (for planning APIs)

When designing voice-agent logic (even if you aren’t using the LiveKit Agents SDK yet), align naming and architecture to:
- session orchestration (“AgentSession”-like)
- tasks / task groups for typed multi-step capture
- workflows for multi-agent handoffs / phase routing
- deterministic tools for DB/API actions and frontend RPC
- explicit turn detection + interruption policy

